talking about me

03:08.013 --> 03:10.407
like I'm your make-a-wish kid.

03:10.494 --> 03:12.322
Don't let him drag you
into his sickness.

03:12.409 --> 03:15.238
It's not right taking advantage
of sad, vulnerable women.

03:15.325 --> 03:17.240
Don't listen to him, I got
plans to meet ladies this year

03:17.327 --> 03:20.287
that's so good
it surprised even me.

03:20.374 --> 03:22.419
Alright, but I am not
going to throw myself

03:22.506 --> 03:24.421
in front
of a hot woman's car again.

03:24.508 --> 03:29.470
That was dangerous, stupid,
and she didn't even slow down.

03:29.557 --> 03:30.732
Well, that says
more about society

03:30.819 --> 03:32.255
than it does about the plan.

03:32.342 --> 03:33.343
You take that scheme to Europe

03:33.430 --> 03:35.998
and we'd get all kinds of tail.

03:36.085 --> 03:38.130
Here's an idea, Samuel,
find a girl you like

03:38.218 --> 03:40.307
ask her out on a date...
on your own.

03:40.394 --> 03:43.048
Man, quit filling his head
with crazy ideas!

03:43.135 --> 03:45.312
You're gonna have him going
to singles bars and nightclubs

03:45.399 --> 03:47.575
which is a lot of work,
a lot of money, a lot of talk

03:47.662 --> 03:49.141
and not to mention
the competition.

03:49.229 --> 03:52.014
I do have certain
financial restrictions.

03:52.101 --> 03:53.624
And the accent gets them
to look at me

03:53.711 --> 03:55.496
but eventually they realize
my credit cards

03:55.583 --> 03:58.107
are made of cardboard
and came with my wallet.

03:59.761 --> 04:01.458
That's why you and me
are going off the grid.

04:01.545 --> 04:02.677
A place where lonely women go

04:02.764 --> 04:04.592
to forget all about
Valentine's Day.

04:04.679 --> 04:08.726
You talking a liquor store
or Baskin-Robbins?

04:08.813 --> 04:10.598
Better. A place where
a single man can stroll in

04:10.685 --> 04:11.816
with no agenda other than

04:11.903 --> 04:13.557
"Hey, can I borrow
a cup of detergent?"

04:13.644 --> 04:18.214
Oh, no. You're gonna try
and get laid at a laundromat?

04:18.301 --> 04:21.391
Two quarters in a dryer gets you
30 minutes to chat up a gal.

04:21.478 --> 04:23.611
At a club, you're buying
five-dollar appletinis

04:23.698 --> 04:25.308
which gets you maybe three
minutes and she can walk away

04:25.395 --> 04:28.180
whenever she wants.

04:28.268 --> 04:30.748
That dryer full of underpants
is like a chain around her neck.

04:37.364 --> 04:41.150
I'm sorry, you can't argue
with the math or the logic.

04:42.499 --> 04:46.373
You, sir,
are a perverted genius.

04:46.460 --> 04:48.766
I've got a beautiful,
filthy mind.

04:52.466 --> 04:54.294
Hi. My name's Mike,
and I'm an overeater.

04:54.381 --> 04:55.599
[all]
Hi, Mike.

04:55.686 --> 04:57.384
Well, I sailed
through the holidays

04:57.471 --> 04:59.124
without over-stuffing
my stocking.

04:59.211 --> 05:00.865
And the great thing
about tofurkey is

05:00.952 --> 05:03.172
