with she threw the ring at him

06:33.654 --> 06:35.699
and he ate
the two-pound box of candy.

06:35.786 --> 06:37.832
She threw the ring at me

06:37.919 --> 06:40.051
and I ate the two-pound
box of candy.

06:40.138 --> 06:41.401
I called it, right?

06:41.488 --> 06:44.099
Get off your high horse,
this man is hurting.

06:44.186 --> 06:48.277
That was ten years
and 113 pounds ago.

06:48.364 --> 06:50.627
As hard as it is
for me to even think

06:50.714 --> 06:53.717
of putting myself out there..

06:53.804 --> 06:57.373
...somewhere underneath
this protective layer..

06:57.460 --> 07:00.332
...there's still a beating heart

07:00.420 --> 07:02.465
'ready to love again.'

07:04.424 --> 07:06.948
Grab your purse.
Let's beat the traffic.

07:12.127 --> 07:14.172
I'll bet Harry trotted out
that sob story

07:14.259 --> 07:17.001
so everyone would forget about
the guy that lost 40 pounds.

07:17.088 --> 07:18.699
Mike!

07:18.786 --> 07:21.223
Too bad stealing spotlights
doesn't burn calories.

07:21.310 --> 07:23.921
You know, this weight loss
is making you kind of a jerk.

07:24.008 --> 07:26.315
[chuckles]
Right?

07:26.402 --> 07:28.404
You know, my heart
really goes out to Harry.

07:28.491 --> 07:30.319
I-I get that he can be
a little annoying

07:30.406 --> 07:32.060
and kind of a know-it-all..

07:32.147 --> 07:35.411
And his clothes are weird
and his breath is bad.

07:35.498 --> 07:38.240
Sometimes he forgets to wipe
those little crusty things

07:38.327 --> 07:40.895
out from the corner of his eyes.

07:40.982 --> 07:42.984
His nose hairs looks like
there's a family of spiders

07:43.071 --> 07:44.725
living in there.

07:44.812 --> 07:47.467
But nevertheless,
he still deserves love.

07:47.554 --> 07:49.251
