the clowns are covered up.

12:54.948 --> 12:59.213
Oh, yeah, you can stick
a red nose on anything.

12:59.300 --> 13:01.693
You and Mike are just
staying in tonight?

13:01.781 --> 13:04.435
Yeah, if we can get
the rest of you on your way.

13:04.522 --> 13:06.611
That's her sweet way of
saying, "get the hell out."

13:06.698 --> 13:09.092
To me, she always just says,
"get the hell out."

13:09.179 --> 13:11.878
aw, Vince, get the hell out.

13:14.968 --> 13:16.186
I'm ready.

13:16.273 --> 13:17.797
Is Larry here?

13:17.884 --> 13:19.320
Hey, first of all, it's Harry.

13:19.407 --> 13:21.104
And second of all,
you can't let him see you

13:21.191 --> 13:22.497
dressed like that.

13:22.584 --> 13:24.020
What's wrong with my outfit?

13:24.107 --> 13:25.413
Nothing, but these
are supposed to look like

13:25.500 --> 13:26.762
they're on the inside
trying to get out

13:26.849 --> 13:30.461
not on the outside
trying to get in.

13:30.548 --> 13:32.289
I've tried controlling them,
but they kind of have

13:32.376 --> 13:34.378
a mind of their own.

13:34.465 --> 13:35.771
Well, if you can't
reason with them

13:35.858 --> 13:36.859
then strap them down.

13:36.946 --> 13:37.947
Are you talking about a bra?

13:38.034 --> 13:39.819
At least. Go.

13:41.951 --> 13:45.563
Am I doing a good deed or taping
a hamster to a skyrocket?

13:53.658 --> 13:55.704
Ah, good, we
beat the crowd.

13:57.271 --> 13:59.142
Man, this place
gonna be hopping

13:59.229 --> 14:00.709
in a couple of hours.

14:00.796 --> 14:02.276
A couple of hours?

14:02.363 --> 14:05.409
I should've brought
my comforter and bed linens.

14:05.496 --> 14:07.150
No, man. You don't want
to bring your bedroom here.

14:07.237 --> 14:09.457
You want to bring them
to your bedroom.

14:09.544 --> 14:11.372
Socks, blue jeans,
underpants.

14:11.459 --> 14:12.416
And everything prewashed

14:12.503 --> 14:15.376
so there's no nasty surprises.

14:15.463 --> 14:16.943
A piece of information
you might've shared

14:17.030 --> 14:19.684
with me before we got here.

14:19.771 --> 14:23.036
I'm carrying
a basket full of funk.

14:23.123 --> 14:24.951
No worries, your untidy-whities
are gonna get washed

14:25.038 --> 14:27.127
like, three or four times
before the evening's out.

14:27.214 --> 14:29.259
I might have to borrow
some quarters from you.

14:29.346 --> 14:31.435
[chuckles]
I don't have any quarters.

14:31.522 --> 14:33.524
See, I just got a crisp
$100 bill, so I can walk up

14:33.611 --> 14:34.961
to a lady and say, "Excuse
me, can you break a hundred?

14:35.048 --> 14:37.964
'Cause I don't have
anything smaller."

14:39.791 --> 14:41.924
If you didn't have
anything smaller

14:42.011 --> 14:44.927
why wouldn't you own
your own washer and dryer?

14:47.799 --> 14:49.410
Hey, you gonna ask a lot of
questions or you want to listen

14:49.497 --> 14:50.890
and learn something?

14:50.977 --> 14:52.848
I'm sorry.
I'm just nervous.

14:52.935 --> 14:54.545
Now, just remember, they
call it "getting lucky"

14:54.632 --> 14:56.721
but luck is the residue
of design.

14:56.808 --> 14:59.550
That's why I brought
a bottle of woolite

14:59.637 --> 15:03.119
so I can offer a little cap
full for their delicates.

15:03.206 --> 15:04.425
Thus bringing up the topic

15:04.512 --> 15:06.253
of their panties
and undergarments

15:06.340 --> 15:09.996
without mentioning
their unmentionables.

15:10.083 --> 15:11.823
This is not my first time
at the laundromat.

15:11.911 --> 15:13.825
Hey-ey-ey, don't load
the dryer next to mine.

15:13.913 --> 15:15.392
Why not?

15:15.479 --> 15:19.092
Questioning me again.
We've got to spread out.

15:19.179 --> 15:22.095
Otherwise, they're gonna
think we're a gay couple.

15:22.182 --> 15:24.619
Got it.

15:24.706 --> 15:26.229
But if we were a gay couple

15:26.316 --> 15:29.798
we would not be spending
Valentine's Day in a laundromat.

15:29.885 --> 15:31.365
- What?
- I'm just saying..

15:31.452 --> 15:33.628
I'd insist you take me
someplace nice.

15:44.421 --> 15:45.770
[sighs]
You know what?

15:45.857 --> 15:47.250
I don't think he's coming.

15:47.337 --> 15:48.860
Oh, it's probably just traffic

15:48.948 --> 15:51.472
it being, you know,
Valentine's Day and all.

15:51.559 --> 15:55.258
Yeah. Could be anything. Maybe
he stepped in front of a bus.

15:55.345 --> 15:57.869
Or maybe the line
at the florist is long.

15:57.957 --> 16:00.872
I'm-I'm sure he's not standing
you up, right, Mike?

16:00.960 --> 16:01.961
No way.

16:02.048 --> 16:03.353
Well, I'm not just gonna

16:03.440 --> 16:04.833
sit around here
wasting my time.

16:04.920 --> 16:08.054
I'll be upstairs
smoking a bowl.

16:08.141 --> 16:09.794
Don't get too comfortable.

16:09.881 --> 16:11.796
Any minute,
that-that sweet fella

16:11.883 --> 16:13.973
is gonna be at our front door.

16:14.060 --> 16:16.018
[whispers]
Where is that idiot?

16:16.105 --> 16:17.367
I didn't want to set Harry up

16:17.454 --> 16:18.716
with your sister
in the first place.

16:18.803 --> 16:20.109
Don't split hairs.
Just call him.

16:20.196 --> 16:21.458
I'm not getting
in the middle of this.

16:21.545 --> 16:23.243
Hey, it's Valentine's Day.

16:23.330 --> 16:24.766
Do you want to get
lucky tonight or not?

16:24.853 --> 16:28.030
You're ovulating now,
you got no choice.

16:28.117 --> 16:30.250
Damn it. Just call him!

16:31.120 --> 16:32.948
Fine.

16:35.820 --> 16:38.171
[cell phone ringing in distance]

16:43.698 --> 16:46.048
[ringing continues]

16:49.225 --> 16:50.487
Don't be mad at me.

16:50.574 --> 16:52.446
And if you hit me,
don't hit me in the face

16:52.533 --> 16:56.189
'cause I'm getting
a new Costco Card on Monday.

16:56.276 --> 16:57.494
What are you doing
out here, Harry?

16:57.581 --> 16:59.627
Victoria's been waiting
for you all night.

16:59.714 --> 17:02.064
I can't do this, Mike.

17:02.151 --> 17:04.023
I'm standing on a crescent moon
reaching for a star

17:04.110 --> 17:06.068
and it's too far to fall.

17:06.155 --> 17:08.288
'Kay, save the poetry
for the lady.

17:08.375 --> 17:09.550
And why are you
getting so nervous?

17:09.637 --> 17:10.855
It's just dinner.

17:10.942 --> 17:12.727
Dinner with an angel.

17:12.814 --> 17:14.163
And I'm just a troll

17:14.250 --> 17:17.253
with an inordinate amount
of ear hair.

17:17.340 --> 17:19.299
Don't talk about my friend
Harry that way.

17:19.386 --> 17:20.604
You're a great guy.

17:20.691 --> 17:23.172
You're kind
and you're sensitive..

17:23.259 --> 17:26.610
...and one other thing.

17:26.697 --> 17:30.614
But what if I blow it and ruin
my last chance at love?

17:30.701 --> 17:33.313
Well, pal, I can't guarantee

17:33.400 --> 17:36.142
that you and Victoria
are gonna be a couple.

17:36.229 --> 17:38.100
But I do know you're
both good people

17:38.187 --> 17:40.668
who deserve to be happy.

17:40.755 --> 17:42.365
It's so easy for you.

17:42.452 --> 17:43.845
What are you talking about?

17:43.932 --> 17:45.325
You didn't know me
before I met Molly.

17:45.412 --> 17:47.196
- I was a mess.
- Impossible.

17:47.283 --> 17:49.546
It's true,
I'd hide out in my apartment

17:49.633 --> 17:53.507
with my two best friends,
Ho Ho and Ding Dong.

17:53.594 --> 17:56.379
Are they really spending
tonight at the laundromat?

17:57.641 --> 17:59.252
Yes, they are.

17:59.339 --> 18:01.080
But you're not.

18:01.167 --> 18:04.561
You're here,
you're looking good

18:04.648 --> 18:07.086
and you got a sweet
woman waiting for you.

18:07.173 --> 18:08.870
You really think
I can do this?

18:08.957 --> 18:10.611
Hey, before I went
out with Molly

18:10.698 --> 18:12.787
I had the same doubts as you.

18:12.874 --> 18:15.094
It's scary to put
yourself out there.

18:15.181 --> 18:17.705
But I did,
and look at us now.

18:17.792 --> 18:21.100
Completely and totally in love.

18:23.406 --> 18:26.453
Where the hell
have you been?

18:26.540 --> 18:29.238
- Harry's here.
- Oh, hi!

18:29.325 --> 18:30.457
Come on in.
Victoria!

18:30.544 --> 18:32.633
He's here!

18:32.720 --> 18:35.244
Aw, don't you look great. Oh,
she's gonna love the flowers.

18:35.331 --> 18:37.420
Actually, these are for you.

18:37.507 --> 18:41.250
Thank you for making a dream
come true.

18:43.034 --> 18:45.428
There it is.
There's that sweet side.

18:45.515 --> 18:48.257
Just...just show her that

18:48.344 --> 18:49.867
and she won't even
notice that hair.

18:49.954 --> 18:51.565
[blowing]

18:54.524 --> 18:57.092
Hey, Harry.

18:57.179 --> 19:00.400
You look very handsome.

19:00.487 --> 19:02.793
Just breathe
and don't lock your knees.

19:02.880 --> 19:05.492
Olympia Dukakis,
Olympia Dukakis..

19:21.725 --> 19:24.554
Probably this location.

19:24.641 --> 19:25.947
[sighs]

19:26.034 --> 19:27.557
I bet the laundromat
near the bus station

19:27.644 --> 19:29.342
is crawling with
lonely, dejected tail

19:29.429 --> 19:31.866
looking to get out of town.

19:31.953 --> 19:33.041
Plus, if they can't
afford to fly

19:33.128 --> 19:36.305
they ain't gonna
be too picky.

19:36.392 --> 19:38.177
Carl, can we please
just go home

19:38.264 --> 19:39.569
while we have
a little bit of dignity

19:39.656 --> 19:42.746
and some of our clothes
still fit us?

19:42.833 --> 19:44.531
Hey, don't be a quitter.

19:44.618 --> 19:47.273
This is the time of night
when Valentine's dates go bad.

19:47.360 --> 19:49.536
Soon, the streets are gonna
be filled with crying women

19:49.623 --> 19:52.539
walking home carrying
their high heels.

19:52.626 --> 19:54.367
So, you're suggesting
we drive around

19:54.454 --> 19:56.238
offering sobbing women
a ride home?

19:56.325 --> 19:59.067
Well, not from inside
the car. That's creepy.

20:00.460 --> 20:02.201
No, y-you park
around the corner

20:02.288 --> 20:03.854
get out and just happen to be
walking in the opposite

20:03.941 --> 20:06.379
direction when they pass by.

20:06.466 --> 20:08.816
"Excuse me, miss.
Is everything okay?

20:08.903 --> 20:11.210
"Aw.

20:12.254 --> 20:14.387
"There, there.

20:15.779 --> 20:18.608
"Everything's just
gonna be fine.

20:18.695 --> 20:22.482
Carl's here."

20:22.569 --> 20:24.614
I've said it once,
I'll say it again

20:24.701 --> 20:27.617
you, sir,
are a perverted genius.

20:27.704 --> 20:28.792
[dryer buzzes]

20:28.879 --> 20:31.273
Oh! My thong
underwear's dry.

20:37.671 --> 20:39.368
[theme music]
